{"word":"στομόω","slug":"στομόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στομόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:στόμα'><el>στόμα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to muzzle</i> or <i>gag</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>(<el>στόμα</el> II) <i>to furnish with an edge</i>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to steel, harden, train for</i> anything, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to fringe, fence</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>; <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, [<el>δράκαινα] ἐχίδναις ἐστομωμένη</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}